            <title>IC-TAG Solutions pursues lean manufacturing</title>
            <description>&lt;p&gt;
	IC-TAG is part of the 33 percent of companies that have already begun with the process of changing one&amp;#39;s lifestyle for the safety and benefit of the environment. Lean manufacturing aligns perfectly with the company&amp;#39;s goals and standards, so the transition came naturally.&lt;br /&gt;
	&lt;br /&gt;
	By understanding the importance and impact of going &amp;ldquo;green,&amp;rdquo; the team works together to reuse, recycle, and save energy. According to Earth Share, &amp;ldquo;It has been estimated that there will be 9 billion people living on planet Earth by the year 2050.&amp;rdquo; Natural resources are becoming more scarce and costly. In order to be prepared for the new growth, IC-TAG&amp;rsquo;s goal is to help preserve natural resources by lowering costs, cutting prices and applying lean manufacturing principles and techniques to eliminate waste and drive efficiencies. Working with partners such as Avery Dennison, IC-TAG Solutions is able to return flanges back to Avery so they can reuse the material and eliminate the need to waste more plastic. By doing this, the company is protecting clients with ever increasing material costs that are incurring. With the help of the company&amp;#39;s employees, IC-TAG is able to give its share towards the environment and community in hopes of setting a positive example in conserving the environment and future. With an emissions-free warehouse, IC-TAG is able to reuse label scraps as packing filler and save energy by unplugging all electrical equipment during downtime.&lt;br /&gt;
	&lt;br /&gt;
	IC-TAG Solutions is embarking phase one of lean manufacturing. With the bold new direction, hope to have an increase in productivity and customer satisfaction. By purchasing labels and RFID products from IC-TAG Solutions, customers can rest assure that they are buying an economical product from an environmentally-friendly RFID manufacturer. IC-TAG looks for new principles, policies, and practices that improve the quality of life for its customers and employees. IC-TAG is also on the look-out to collaborate with partners to ensure lean manufacturing. With a positive outlook, the goal is to strive for long-term success and sustainment.&lt;br /&gt;
	&lt;br /&gt;
	&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;About IC-TAG Solutions Inc.&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
	IC-TAG Solutions is a credited manufacturer of customizable, pressure sensitive labels and tags, specializing in RFID. IC-TAG Solutions provides HF and UHF Radio Frequency Identification (RFID) products and services to companies in manufacturing, U.S. Department of Defense, consumer goods, retail, transportation and logistics, pharmaceuticals and other industries. IC-TAG Solutions integrates RFID inlays into pressure sensitive labels and tags by using various inlay types, substrates and inks to manufacture custom IC-TAG products. IC-TAG Solutions is a member of EPC Global.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/noria/reliableplant/tags/lean_manufacturing/~4/Yd2m7ctBzaw" height="1" width="1" alt=""/&gt;</description>
            <a10:updated>2010-12-30T08:49:10-06:00</a10:updated>
            <a10:content type="text/html" src="http://reliableplant.com/Read/28067/IC-TAG-lean-manufacturing" />
        <feedburner:origLink>http://reliableplant.com/Read/28067/IC-TAG-lean-manufacturing</feedburner:origLink></item>
