            <title>Association for Manufacturing Excellence forms alliance with Productivity Alberta</title>
            <description>&lt;p&gt;
	The Association for Manufacturing Excellence (AME) on October 27 announced its recently formed alliance with the Alberta government&amp;rsquo;s Productivity Alberta (PA) to increase manufacturers&amp;rsquo; productivity.&lt;br /&gt;
	&lt;br /&gt;
	&amp;ldquo;This agreement will take our prior collaboration with PA to a higher level and will enhance organizational experience for all members,&amp;rdquo; says Bill Baker, vice president of alliances for AME. &amp;ldquo;It will provide both AME members and PA clients with new opportunities that will help improve everyone&amp;rsquo;s bottom lines, from networking to world-class knowledge and education.&amp;rdquo;&lt;br /&gt;
	&lt;br /&gt;
	As a result of the formalized partnership, AME members and PA clients will gain access to a multitude of new opportunities and resources, including:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
		Enhanced benchmarking capabilities with a larger and broader comparison group&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
		Greater access to cutting edge thinking, best-practice research and lessons learned&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
		Expanded marketing exposure and recognition&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
		Broadened exposure to networking, knowledge sharing and educational opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	This alliance offers support for AME and PA by promoting events and conferences and sharing articles for print and digital publishing. PA will have access to AME&amp;rsquo;s education and training resources for manufacturers located in Alberta, and support AME&amp;rsquo;s &amp;ldquo;Measure Up For Success&amp;rdquo; conference, June 6-10, 2011, in Calgary. These actions will encourage more effective and efficient learning through benchmarking and knowledge transfer as a way to grow the North American manufacturing and supply chain sectors.&lt;br /&gt;
	&lt;br /&gt;
	For more information on AME and its member benefits, visit &lt;a href="http://click.icptrack.com/icp/relay.php?r=36184429&amp;amp;msgid=535765&amp;amp;act=5KGN&amp;amp;c=280546&amp;amp;destination=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.ame.org"&gt;www.ame.org&lt;/a&gt;. To learn more about Productivity Alberta, visit &lt;a href="http://click.icptrack.com/icp/relay.php?r=36184429&amp;amp;msgid=535765&amp;amp;act=5KGN&amp;amp;c=280546&amp;amp;destination=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.productivityalberta.ca"&gt;www.productivityalberta.ca&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;About the Association for Manufacturing Excellence&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
	The Association for Manufacturing Excellence (AME) is the premier not-for-profit organization dedicated to the journey of continuous improvement and enterprise excellence. AME&amp;rsquo;s membership is composed of a trusted network of volunteers who are committed to leveraging the practitioner-to-practitioner and company-to-company shared-learning experience. Through engaging workshops, seminars, plant tours and industry-leading conferences, AME members are continually discovering and implementing new continuous improvement strategies and best practices. AME offers its members a multitude of valuable resources to help them stay abreast of current industry developments, and improve the skills, competitiveness and overall success of their organizations.&lt;br /&gt;
	&lt;br /&gt;
	&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;About Productivity Alberta&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
	Productivity Alberta is industry&amp;rsquo;s connection to the latest in productivity improvement tools, resources and services.&amp;nbsp; As an industry-guided service, working collaboratively with organizations across the province and beyond, we connect Alberta-based businesses to everything they need to kick start and enhance productivity growth and competitiveness, leading to a healthier bottom line. A program offered by the Government of Alberta through the department of Finance and Enterprise, Productivity Alberta addresses a specific mandate to enhance value-added activity, increase productivity innovation, and build a skilled workforce to improve the long-run competitiveness and sustainability of Alberta&amp;rsquo;s economy.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/noria/reliableplant/tags/lean_manufacturing/~4/0-xR3zhsblE" height="1" width="1" alt=""/&gt;</description>
            <a10:updated>2010-10-27T14:27:40-05:00</a10:updated>
